Screencap from [Black in Tokyo](https://youtu.be/UsXbOxTgCCo) (YouTube video).

A short documentary from 2017 takes a look at the lives of black residents in
Tokyo. Directed by Nigerian-American artist [Amarachi
Nwosu](https://twitter.com/AmaraWorldWide/status/932679393570377730), the film
follows five subjects, with origins ranging from West Africa to the U.S.,
narrating the different cultural challenges and opportunities of living in
Tokyo, Japan. The subjects of the documentary include the owner of a
barbershop, an artist, a DJ and a member of the U.S. Air Force stationed at a
base just outside of Tokyo.

